# Project: [Your Project Name]

## Tech Stack
- Runtime: Node.js 20 with TypeScript 5.x (strict mode)
- Framework: React 19.2 or Latest version
- Testing: Vitest for unit tests, Playwright for e2e
- Styling: Tailwind CSS

## Code Conventions
- Use const by default, let only when reassignment is needed, never var
- Prefer async/await over .then() chains
- Use named exports, not default exports
- Error handling: always use typed errors, never throw raw strings
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components

## Architecture
- API routes go in src/api/
- Business logic lives in src/services/
- Shared types go in src/types/
- Reuse existing patterns -- check for similar implementations before creating new ones

## What NOT to Do
- Do not install new dependencies without asking first
- Do not modify configuration files (.env, tsconfig, package.json) without explicit request
- Do not remove existing tests
- Do not use any as a type -- use unknown and narrow appropriately